dismissalText.commentary: Misbah-ul-Haq run out (Dilshan) 18 (30b 2x4 0x6 48m) SR: 60

dismissalComment.html: thats a direct hit and Misbah has just kept on going. he knows he's short! Just when they were getting to safer ground, Misbah has underestimated Dilshan's prowess at point. Raced in, got a good bounce into his right hand and sent a dead-eye through that capitalised on just the smallest hesitation

but it's gone into his head! This was quicker, shorter rising almost above his head outside off. Took it on unwisely, gets a top edge and Malinga runs up and to his right from mid-on, tumbles and takes a pretty good catch

that's another beauty from Thisara! Dun in sharply, there's too much bounce for Maqsood, the last time that happened he managed to get himself out of the way. This time he fends and gloves it to the keeper. Terrific take behind the stumps as Sanga dives to his left

there's another. It's a procession! No more reviews left, and Wahab is not pleased with the outcome, wanted a second opinion but is surprised to see he can't go for it, Dilshan pats him on the back to send him on his way. Its the bounce again, coupled with a little nip away. The batsman chased it with an open face, although we can't conclusively say there was an edge, but the keeper went up, the bowler went up and so did the finger

headshotImage.caption: Saeed Ajmal player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: bounced out again! Pretty much a replay of Akmal's wicket, perhaps this was a touch slower but he had to drag the bouncer from outside off stump again, poorly judged pull lands in the hands of midwicket. Dolly of a catch

dismissalText.commentary: Mahela Jayawardene c Mohammad Hafeez b Saeed Ajmal 26 (32b 3x4 0x6 33m) SR: 81.25

dismissalComment.html: one run left to win, and Mahela has tapped a doosra to first slip. It went a touch wrong too, a shorter ball outside off and turning further away. He had misread the turn, was originally looking to play it but after he read off the pitch, he thought of pulling away. But wasn't quick enough. Slip does extremely well to grab that. Dilshan has an almost apologetic smile on his face

Wahab is pumped as he gets the ball to shape away late just enough to fox Sanga. The bat pushed in front of him and away from his body, hitting on the up, and perishes

commentTextItems.html: beats point on his left and Dilsha raises his fifty and the victory. It was short and wide again, he backed away, waited a little longer and hammered it past the fielder's reach. Quite a comprehensive ending to a game the hosts have dominated throughout

commentPostTextItems.html: 4.00 pm So it's an early finish, one the loud and proud Dambulla crowd has enjoyed. Spectators were hurtling in through the gates that were thrown open. They hung from the trees, they milled in the stands and their side has played pulled off as emphatic a victory as any. Lasith Malinga has his boy on his arms for the team picture. They're having a lot of fun out there, but here is were I leave you. Thank you for your company and comments, this is Alagappan Muthu signing off

"To come after that defeat in Hambantota, we had to put up our socks. The bowler set the tone, Dhammika and Malinga early and then Thisara," says Angelo Mathews, " I wanted to experiment a little, give Thisara more opportunities and Dhammika has also proven he is a very good bowler in the past few series. The pitch was doing a little bit in the early hours and then it flattened out alittle bit but when you're chasing 100 you should play positive cricket and not block. We'll just have a few days off and train for England. Tough against Pakistan, good balanced team so all the very best for their future tournaments"

Thisara Perera is the Man of the Match and Man of the Series "First of all, I'm proud of my all round performances. its a good wicket to bowl, as a bowling unit we've done really well. It's just confidence, last match I bowled well and came back strongly. I'm going to work on my bowling and keep getting better. Try my best, and if I have more chances to play more than 10 overs I'll do my best"

3.50 pm "The wicket is a bit different in Dambulla. Spungy bounce you need to get used to, but if you scored 240 or 250, that would have been useful. But we lost too many wickets early," says Misbah-ul-Haq "Fawad and I were trying to be there till the 30th over. We tried to put up a fight, but again we lost too many wickets. We have a little bit of a picture of what we want to do in the coming series. We will play the world cup in Australia, and the management will think about that. Australia series is really important, we have to get the right combination. The crowd is very good, we always enjoy here. The result hasn't been great, but the experience in Sri Lanka was"

Genial handshakes to complete what has been an enthralling tour. It is a shame the the final match was so one-sided, after the way the ODIs had begun. Saeed Ajmal was missed by Pakistan, but when he did return their batsmen folded horribly. Despite Pakistan's rich bowling resources, 101 was never going to be defendable. Stay tuned for the presentation
Sohaib: "Pakistan must have seriously upset the sponsors, they've not gotten enough air-time."

commentPreTextItems.html: Aditi: "Do you think there's some sort of an infection flying around Cricket where perfectly good batsmen suddenly cannot find a run? Re: Virat, and Sanga? :("

dismissalText.commentary: Sharjeel Khan c Jayawardene b Prasad 0 (6b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: he has not been keen to get forward, too early in his innings perhaps and that becomes his undoing. Thick outside edge flies to second slip! Good length ball goes on with the angle across the left-hander, he helps Prasad by staying stuck on the crease and reaching with his hands. Tame push, nick produced, catch pouched

dismissalText.commentary: Ahmed Shehzad c Perera b Prasad 10 (21b 1x4 0x6 32m) SR: 47.61

dismissalComment.html: that's the pressure talking! And some might argue Pakistan have placed it on themselves, to an extent. Drags a good length ball, with no feet, right into the hands of mid-on. Too early to be manufacturing strokes, especially against the bowler who has looked most likely to pick up wickets

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Hafeez lbw b Malinga 1 (16b 0x4 0x6 27m) SR: 6.25

dismissalComment.html: huuuuge appeal for lbw and finally the umpire is persuaded. But the batsman is not. Goes for a review straight away. Pitched on a good length and nibbled in just enough, Hafeez was flicking across the line and misses. It's a marginal call, and the ball tracker says it would have clipped leg stump to it stays with umpires call. Review lost, top order all but silenced

headshotImage.caption: Angelo Mathews, player page headshot cutout 2023
headshotImage.longCaption: Angelo Mathews, player page headshot cutout 2023

dismissalText.commentary: Misbah-ul-Haq run out (Dilshan) 18 (30b 2x4 0x6 48m) SR: 60

dismissalComment.html: thats a direct hit and Misbah has just kept on going. he knows he's short! Just when they were getting to safer ground, Misbah has underestimated Dilshan's prowess at point. Raced in, got a good bounce into his right hand and sent a dead-eye through that capitalised on just the smallest hesitation

dismissalText.commentary: Umar Akmal c Malinga b Perera 7 (9b 0x4 1x6 11m) SR: 77.77

dismissalComment.html: but it's gone into his head! This was quicker, shorter rising almost above his head outside off. Took it on unwisely, gets a top edge and Malinga runs up and to his right from mid-on, tumbles and takes a pretty good catch

dismissalText.commentary: Sohaib Maqsood c †Sangakkara b Perera 7 (9b 1x4 0x6 18m) SR: 77.77

dismissalComment.html: that's another beauty from Thisara! Dun in sharply, there's too much bounce for Maqsood, the last time that happened he managed to get himself out of the way. This time he fends and gloves it to the keeper. Terrific take behind the stumps as Sanga dives to his left

headshotImage.caption: Seekkuge Prasanna player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Seekkuge Prasanna player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Shahid Afridi c Perera b Prasanna 2 (4b 0x4 0x6 5m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: too much intent, of the needless kind. He danced down the track, opened the face to scythe it over point. Made a little too much room to enable the stroke, but worse, there is a sweeper in place, he has to run a little to his right and picks up a reverse cup to send Prasanna on a lap!

dismissalText.commentary: Wahab Riaz c †Sangakkara b Perera 0 (2b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: there's another. It's a procession! No more reviews left, and Wahab is not pleased with the outcome, wanted a second opinion but is surprised to see he can't go for it, Dilshan pats him on the back to send him on his way. Its the bounce again, coupled with a little nip away. The batsman chased it with an open face, although we can't conclusively say there was an edge, but the keeper went up, the bowler went up and so did the finger

headshotImage.caption: Saeed Ajmal player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Saeed Ajmal player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Saeed Ajmal player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Saeed Ajmal player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Saeed Ajmal c Jayawardene b Perera 6 (15b 1x4 0x6 13m) SR: 40

dismissalComment.html: bounced out again! Pretty much a replay of Akmal's wicket, perhaps this was a touch slower but he had to drag the bouncer from outside off stump again, poorly judged pull lands in the hands of midwicket. Dolly of a catch

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Irfan b Herath 5 (9b 1x4 0x6 21m) SR: 55.55

dismissalComment.html: not quite! This was flighted on off stump, Irfan went for a slog sweep but the ball swooped under his bat and rattles his stumps. Fawad stands there, stunned at this collapse for a few moments.

dismissalText.commentary: Upul Tharanga b Mohammad Irfan 14 (17b 2x4 0x6 34m) SR: 82.35

dismissalComment.html: leans into a cover drive, only he ends up inside edging onto middle stump! Invitingly full, even if that doesn't seem Irfan's natural length, it was wide enough to chase but the batsmen mistimed it. Good way to go to the break for Pakistan

dismissalText.commentary: Tillakaratne Dilshan not out 50 (55b 9x4 0x6 84m) SR: 90.9

dismissalText.long: c Mohammad Hafeez b Wahab Riaz
dismissalText.commentary: Kumar Sangakkara c Mohammad Hafeez b Wahab Riaz 2 (5b 0x4 0x6 12m) SR: 40

dismissalComment.html: he's got him! Lovely delivery, lured the batsman on the drive and the outside edge is safely pouched at second slip. Wahab is pumped as he gets the ball to shape away late just enough to fox Sanga. The bat pushed in front of him and away from his body, hitting on the up, and perishes

headshotImage.caption: Saeed Ajmal player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Saeed Ajmal player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.long: c Mohammad Hafeez b Saeed Ajmal
dismissalText.commentary: Mahela Jayawardene c Mohammad Hafeez b Saeed Ajmal 26 (32b 3x4 0x6 33m) SR: 81.25

dismissalComment.html: one run left to win, and Mahela has tapped a doosra to first slip. It went a touch wrong too, a shorter ball outside off and turning further away. He had misread the turn, was originally looking to play it but after he read off the pitch, he thought of pulling away. But wasn't quick enough. Slip does extremely well to grab that. Dilshan has an almost apologetic smile on his face
